HTML Page Structure
1. Document Declaration
	<!DOCTYPE html>
2. Document Scope
	<html> </html>
3. Sections in Document Scope
	<head> </head>
	<body> </body>

4. Head Section
	<title>
	<link>
	<meta>

		    Meta in HTML
		    -------------------
- Meta represents "Meta Data".
- Meta data contains information about your page given to browser and SEO. [Search Engine Optimization].
- Meta is used by browser to make the page responsive.
- A responsive page can fit content according to device of client.
  [Mobile, Tab, PC, Laptop, Watch]
- Meta is one option for making page responsive.

Meta for Responsive Page:
=====================

name=viewport	: defines the type of device [mobile, watch, tab]
		  defines the orientation of device.

content		: width fits to device width.
		  initial scale set to 100% [zoom].

Syntax:
 <head>
  <meta name="viewport"  content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
 </head>


To Test on Various devices download:

- Go to Google Chrome browser
- Type in address bar
	Chrome://apps
- Click on "Web Store"
- Search for "Mobile Simulator"
- Add to Chrome.

Meta for SEO:
================
<meta  charset="utf-8">

       charset  : It is used by crawlers to understand the type of language
	      used for website. Language type is identified according
	      to charset.

	      UTF  - Unicode Transformation Format

	      8 bit		english
	      16 bit		china, japan, korean, hindi, tel, tamil
	      32 bit		arabic
	
<meta name="keywords"  content="some keywords..">

	  
   Keywords 	: are the words used by crawlers to find your
		  page and show in results.


<meta name="description"  content="something about your site">

    Description 	: is summary of your website shown in search
		  results.


Meta Request Header
=================
- It is used by browser to manage request to any website.

<meta http-equiv="refresh"  content="5">


Summary:
<head>
 <meta name="viewport"  content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
 <meta charset="utf-8">
 <meta name="keywords"  content="Shopping Online, Buy Online, Mobile Online">
 <meta name="description" content="Amazon is online shopping store with great offers..">
 <meta http-equiv="refresh"  content="5">
</head>


4. Style	:  It is used to embed styles / css in your page.

	  <head>
	   <style>
	        selector {
	         }
	  </style>
	</head>

5. Script	: It is used to embed script and files
	
	<head>
	<script>
	   function f1() { 
	   }
	</script>
	</head>


